comment_data.body:
@merwok Yes, it is.
For this PR, I just replaced the `assert`s and did not really look at the rest of the code, but, probably, the change you proposed will still fit into the topic of the PR, so I will add it.
Thanks for the comment.

> Because it is not a test but an assertion about the test code itself. Like an assert in normal production code.

@scoder That doesn't mean we can't use `unittest`'s `assert` for this part, does it?
In case of problems, the error will still occur, but we will have a more beautiful and understandable message about it in our hands.

This `msg = msg` is not supported by 2.7, so the output will be `AssertionError: Exception not raised` rather than `AssertionError: Exception not raised : Invalid Cython code ...` as for other tested versions.
I think this is negligible compared to improving the quality of the code.
@scoder If you also do not think this is especially important, you can resolve this conversation.
